<i>I'll head over now to join you.</i>

140
00:09:51.924 --> 00:09:53.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Françoise] He hung up.

141
00:09:53.217 --> 00:09:55.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wow, what the hell
is that guy thinking?

142
00:10:01.475 --> 00:10:03.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All this high-speed
running around you're doing

143
00:10:03.644 --> 00:10:05.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is futile. Give it up.

144
00:10:05.521 --> 00:10:07.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

145
00:10:07.523 --> 00:10:08.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never!

146
00:10:10.985 --> 00:10:14.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Really, now,
think you can thwart me, do you?

147
00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:17.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because you're working
to wipe out the human race.

148
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:26.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

149
00:10:26.167 --> 00:10:29.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There seems to be
a slight misunderstanding here.

150
00:10:29.462 --> 00:10:33.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Humankind has given up
on its evolutionary progress.

151
00:10:33.257 --> 00:10:36.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doing so ensures
its self-destruction.

152
00:10:36.969 --> 00:10:40.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's precisely
why I want to guide them,

153
00:10:40.097 --> 00:10:41.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to help them become

154
00:10:41.349 --> 00:10:43.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
better versions
of their current selves.

155
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:47.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe] That's a self-righteous
way of looking at it.

156
00:10:47.229 --> 00:10:49.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They don't need your help.

157
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:52.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Humans always change
of their own free will.

158
00:10:52.735 --> 00:10:54.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's why I'm here,

159
00:10:54.445 --> 00:10:56.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to ensure
they continue living free...

160
00:10:57.990 --> 00:10:59.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and that's what I intend to do!

161
00:11:05.581 --> 00:11:08.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There was a time when I tried
to save foolish humans,

162
00:11:08.542 --> 00:11:11.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
those full of pride
and spirit like you,

163
00:11:11.462 --> 00:11:12.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but then....

164
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

165
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:16.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I realized
that even with my power,

166
00:11:16.842 --> 00:11:20.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it wasn't nearly adequate
to save the entire human race.

167
00:11:20.638 --> 00:11:22.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>What's different now, Emperor?</i>

168
00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:25.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>How are you going</i>
<i>to save humanity this time?</i>

169
00:11:27.436 --> 00:11:29.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By resetting it.

170
00:11:30.773 --> 00:11:31.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Resetting?

171
00:11:33.025 --> 00:11:34.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Emperor...

172
00:11:35.403 --> 00:11:36.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
insanity.

173
00:11:43.244 --> 00:11:47.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you go that route,
it will destroy us, too.

174
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:49.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A dangerous battlefield

175
00:11:49.708 --> 00:11:52.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is no place for a young
female civilian to hang out.

176
00:11:52.711 --> 00:11:54.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So sorry.

177
00:11:54.296 --> 00:11:56.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no. I should apologize.

178
00:11:56.924 --> 00:11:59.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm the one who forced
all of you back into battle.

179
00:11:59.885 --> 00:12:01.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't give it a second thought.

180
00:12:01.679 --> 00:12:03.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Remember,
we're Zero-Zero cyborgs.

181
00:12:03.722 --> 00:12:05.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's our mission.
It's what we do.

182
00:12:06.142 --> 00:12:09.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to promise
that you'll all survive!

183
00:12:09.103 --> 00:12:10.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell Heinrich, too!

184
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:13.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Consider the message delivered.

185
00:12:24.034 --> 00:12:25.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

186
00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:26.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What's that?
-[rotors thrumming]

187
00:12:32.918 --> 00:12:34.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[G.B.]
Sorry to keep you waiting.

188
00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:36.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise]
It's the U.N. Guardians.

189
00:12:36.130 --> 00:12:37.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] Crap, so we can't exactly

190
00:12:37.673 --> 00:12:39.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
blast 'em
to hell and back, huh?

191
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:41.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In that case, let's just
go meet Joe and Ivan.

192
00:13:09.830 --> 00:13:11.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

193
00:13:20.174 --> 00:13:22.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ivan] <i>What do you</i>
<i>mean by reset</i>?

194
00:13:23.052 --> 00:13:25.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just what the word implies.

195
00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:27.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When a program suffers a glitch,

196
00:13:27.973 --> 00:13:30.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it cannot be
fundamentally resolved

197
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:32.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
through makeshift adjustments.

198
00:13:32.478 --> 00:13:35.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You must start again
from the basic design.

199
00:13:35.648 --> 00:13:37.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By doing what?

200
00:13:37.441 --> 00:13:39.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will accomplish this

201
00:13:39.193 --> 00:13:42.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
by fusing Ivan's telepathy
with my own powers,

202
00:13:42.154 --> 00:13:45.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then erase
humanity's useless memories.

203
00:13:45.574 --> 00:13:47.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

204
00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:49.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No way will I let you do that!

205
00:13:52.456 --> 00:13:54.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

206
00:13:58.003 --> 00:13:59.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's this?

207
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:01.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[thunder crashing]

208
00:14:09.765 --> 00:14:11.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[growls]

209
00:14:17.064 --> 00:14:17.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh?

210
00:14:18.857 --> 00:14:19.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

211
00:14:22.027 --> 00:14:24.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] Igarashi, is that you?

212
00:14:24.238 --> 00:14:25.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry to make you wait.

213
00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:27.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it looks as if

214
00:14:27.324 --> 00:14:29.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
our lead actor has
just taken the stage.

215
00:14:34.748 --> 00:14:36.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Françoise] A missile?

216
00:14:36.166 --> 00:14:38.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I don't think so. That's--

217
00:14:38.252 --> 00:14:40.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunfire echoing]

218
00:14:45.259 --> 00:14:47.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

219
00:14:47.261 --> 00:14:48.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

220
00:14:52.099 --> 00:14:54.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pyotr] As ordered by my master,

221
00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:57.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I shall now commence my mission
and dispose of you.

222
00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:58.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pyotr?

223
00:14:59.064 --> 00:15:01.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[growling]

224
00:15:08.741 --> 00:15:10.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh? Where'd he go?

225
00:15:10.492 --> 00:15:11.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ai-yah!

226
00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:13.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[G.B. grunts]

227
00:15:13.245 --> 00:15:14.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn you!

228
00:15:17.416 --> 00:15:20.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

229
00:15:24.423 --> 00:15:27.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>009, it's a gravity wave.</i>

230
00:15:27.343 --> 00:15:29.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How many powers does he have?

231
00:15:29.637 --> 00:15:31.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only one.

232
00:15:39.647 --> 00:15:40.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh?

233
00:15:41.982 --> 00:15:43.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Ivan shudders]
-Ivan!

234
00:15:44.401 --> 00:15:45.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait.

235
00:15:46.403 --> 00:15:48.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do not want to hurt you, Ivan.

236
00:15:50.574 --> 00:15:51.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Oh?</i>

237
00:15:51.825 --> 00:15:53.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>What's this?</i>

238
00:15:53.494 --> 00:15:54.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] Ivan!

239
00:15:54.787 --> 00:15:56.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Emperor] An anti-field.

240
00:15:56.830 --> 00:15:59.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you mind timing out
for a little while?

241
00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:02.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your demise gains me nothing.

242
00:16:02.252 --> 00:16:04.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cannot claim
your cyborg powers.

243
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:11.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is this?

244
00:16:11.762 --> 00:16:14.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How can he possibly
move faster than me?

245
00:16:14.181 --> 00:16:17.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[scoffs]
I'm not moving fast at all.

246
00:16:17.726 --> 00:16:19.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That so-called Accelerator Mode

247
00:16:20.062 --> 00:16:23.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
may be boosting your
thought processes to accommodate

248
00:16:23.607 --> 00:16:26.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
your physicality's
increased velocity.

249
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:29.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-As regards speed of thought...
-[crushing]

250
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:33.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
having lived for 3,000 years,
I leave you in the dust.

251
00:16:33.826 --> 00:16:35.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe gasps]

252
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:38.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're an epic disappointment.

253
00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:42.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had hopes for you
after hearing what Linker said.

254
00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:47.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Catalina exhales]

255
00:16:47.715 --> 00:16:49.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[telepathically]
<i>009...</i>

256
00:16:49.758 --> 00:16:52.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I know you have more power</i>
<i>than you're showing,</i>

257
00:16:52.344 --> 00:16:55.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the power to transcend time.</i>

258
00:17:24.376 --> 00:17:25.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

259
00:17:27.379 --> 00:17:28.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
002!

260
00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:32.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>002! What's wrong?! 002!</i>

261
00:17:37.097 --> 00:17:38.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, thanks for that.

262
00:17:38.390 --> 00:17:39.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I owe you one. Huh?

263
00:17:45.355 --> 00:17:48.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Igarashi yells]

264
00:17:48.442 --> 00:17:49.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Igarashi!

265
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:52.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where'd he go?

266
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:57.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's like a Joe who can fly.

267
00:17:57.409 --> 00:18:01.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll thank you not to compare me
to that piece of junk.

268
00:18:01.246 --> 00:18:04.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am a member of a new breed,
chosen by the gods.

269
00:18:04.666 --> 00:18:07.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After disposing
of you cyborg defects,

270
00:18:07.669 --> 00:18:09.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I shall help guide humanity

271
00:18:09.379 --> 00:18:11.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as a proud servant
of those gods.

272
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:14.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hah! You're crazy as a bedbug.

273
00:18:17.846 --> 00:18:22.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Heh. You're actually
putting up a fight, Igarashi.

274
00:18:22.267 --> 00:18:24.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't mock me, you bastard!

275
00:18:29.399 --> 00:18:31.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[wind blowing]

276
00:18:33.403 --> 00:18:34.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

277
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:41.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[screams]

278
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:44.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crackling]

279
00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:46.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

280
00:18:48.335 --> 00:18:51.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

281
00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:52.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clang]

282
00:18:55.759 --> 00:18:57.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Linker...

283
00:18:57.094 --> 00:18:59.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm so disappointed in you.

284
00:18:59.847 --> 00:19:01.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Catalina.

285
00:19:01.348 --> 00:19:05.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Emperor] I know exactly
what you're thinking.

286
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:06.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ivan gasps]

287
00:19:06.728 --> 00:19:10.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I possess the same linking power
as you do.

288
00:19:10.607 --> 00:19:12.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

289
00:19:12.317 --> 00:19:14.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could you have my power?

290
00:19:14.736 --> 00:19:16.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I see now, Emperor.</i>

291
00:19:16.905 --> 00:19:19.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Your ability is to copy</i>
<i>the powers of others.</i>

292
00:19:20.617 --> 00:19:22.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right, Ivan.

293
00:19:22.411 --> 00:19:26.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can reproduce any power
that I come into contact with.

294
00:19:26.248 --> 00:19:27.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can't.

295
00:19:27.708 --> 00:19:29.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The day he...

296
00:19:33.463 --> 00:19:35.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I make a copy,

297
00:19:35.132 --> 00:19:38.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
leaving the donor's power
in place,

298
00:19:38.302 --> 00:19:43.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and so, they never
realize it's mine.

299
00:19:44.725 --> 00:19:46.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

300
00:19:46.810 --> 00:19:48.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By the way, Linker...

301
00:19:50.272 --> 00:19:53.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what is the reason you are here?

302
00:19:58.113 --> 00:19:59.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are...

303
00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:04.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Emperor.

304
00:20:06.538 --> 00:20:09.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What-- What am I doing here?

305
00:20:13.128 --> 00:20:14.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As I recall, your mission

306
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:17.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was to do away with the cyborgs,
was it not?

307
00:20:18.133 --> 00:20:21.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right. I went
to Lake Superior with Igarashi.

308
00:20:22.054 --> 00:20:25.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, Catalina. What'd you do?

309
00:20:25.432 --> 00:20:28.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I erased the memories
of your bond.

310
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:34.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They may be a precious
and cherished thing to humans,

311
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:36.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but if one were
to erase them completely,

312
00:20:36.818 --> 00:20:39.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then there would be
no more grief in the world.

313
00:20:39.613 --> 00:20:42.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would be a good thing, yes?

314
00:20:42.324 --> 00:20:44.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could you?

315
00:20:46.328 --> 00:20:47.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
009.

316
00:20:58.215 --> 00:20:59.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

317
00:21:01.301 --> 00:21:02.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

318
00:21:06.348 --> 00:21:07.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] Damn it.

319
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:10.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't those damn Savior tanks
have any flaws?

320
00:21:10.310 --> 00:21:12.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They do, but...

321
00:21:12.396 --> 00:21:14.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>What should I do</i>?

322
00:21:14.106 --> 00:21:15.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold him there.

323
00:21:15.565 --> 00:21:17.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>10 seconds should do it.</i>

324
00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:18.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

325
00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:19.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

326
00:21:22.572 --> 00:21:24.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>This guy, for 10 seconds</i>?

327
00:21:25.033 --> 00:21:26.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Impossible, right?

328
00:21:26.576 --> 00:21:28.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I can do it!

329
00:21:28.912 --> 00:21:30.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[tires squeal]

330
00:21:31.581 --> 00:21:33.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet grunting]

331
00:21:39.089 --> 00:21:40.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yelps]

332
00:21:45.595 --> 00:21:46.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

333
00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:49.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. I'm losing control.

334
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:54.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Igarashi, it ain't over yet!

335
00:21:54.938 --> 00:21:56.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold on a little longer!

336
00:21:58.317 --> 00:21:59.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crash]

337
00:21:59.484 --> 00:22:00.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn you.

338
00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:08.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yelling]

339
00:22:10.245 --> 00:22:12.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you actually
going to fight me

340
00:22:12.122 --> 00:22:13.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with your bare hands?

341
00:22:16.418 --> 00:22:18.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever it takes, you tin can!

342
00:22:20.380 --> 00:22:22.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet grunting]

343
00:22:27.345 --> 00:22:29.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As long as I'm
holding on to you,

344
00:22:29.347 --> 00:22:31.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you can't accelerate
worth a damn.

345
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:34.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pyotr] What are you doing?

346
00:22:38.023 --> 00:22:40.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet yells]

347
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:42.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pyotr] Damn you!

348
00:22:50.243 --> 00:22:52.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

349
00:23:02.547 --> 00:23:04.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans] I made a mistake.

350
00:23:04.758 --> 00:23:07.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, my functions
are still intact.

351
00:23:13.558 --> 00:23:14.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Igarashi] <i>Jet</i>.

352
00:23:20.273 --> 00:23:22.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Some nice control there.

353
00:23:24.277 --> 00:23:25.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

354
00:23:25.529 --> 00:23:27.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Igarashi.

355
00:23:27.489 --> 00:23:29.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So long, Pyotr.

356
00:23:32.369 --> 00:23:33.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

357
00:23:49.010 --> 00:23:51.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[ballad playing]

358
00:23:58.770 --> 00:24:00.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[singing in Japanese]

